{
  "texts": [
    "These models have somewhat solved the problem of predicting multivariate, heteroskedastic time series with nonlinear relationships.",
    "However, they suffer from poor generalization, which leads to limited prediction accuracy.Deep learning (DL) models (Fig. 1) have greatly improved the nonlinear modeling capabilities of TSF in recent years.",
    "These models are constructed with neural network structures with powerful nonlinear modeling capabilities to learn complex patterns and feature representations in time series automatically.",
    "Therefore, DL is an effective solution for TSF and many other problems related to TSF, such as hierarchical time series forecasting [32], intermittent time series forecasting [33], and sparse multivariate time series forecasting [34] asynchronous time series forecasting [35,36].",
    "It has extended some multi-objective, multigranular forecasting scenarios [37] and multi-modal time series forecasting scenarios [38, Fig. 1 The development history of TSF algorithms based on deep learning 1 3 39]."
  ]
}